        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 2:43AM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 242 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 11 miles southeast of Atwood to 4 miles southeast of
Colby to 3 miles north of Monument. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Automated weather station at Colby airport reported a gust
of 54 MPH at 2:35 AM CT.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Gem around 245 AM CDT.
Oakley around 250 AM CDT.
Rexford around 300 AM CDT.

Other locations in the path of these storms include Menlo.

This includes Interstate 70 in Kansas between mile markers 51 and 75.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
